      "body" : "To clarify \"real issue\" from my perspective;  especially on random consumer software/hardware we cannot reasonably expect that it will _never_ become corrupted on an unclean power off; because there has been quite a bit of broken stuff out there that scribbled randomly on the disk in the case.  But at the very least it should be rare.  If it isn't rare it may indicate another problem.\r\n",
